[MESSAGE]Congratulations on owning your very first coffee shop! In this tutorial, we'll talk about how you can set up the counter area of your café and prepare the menu selection that you will offer to your customers.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]By opening the _Recipe Menu_, you can see that the recipes available to you are different from those of the restaurants. In here, the menu is divided into five categories - _Hot Coffee_, _Iced Coffee_, _Tea_, _Other Drinks_ and _Food_. Just like restaurant recipes, different coffee shop menu items can have different facility requirements in order to prepare them.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]One thing that you should always remember when opening a coffee shop is that it requires both a kitchen and a counter area to work properly. It should also be noted that a number of facilities can only be added when there is a counter area available. As you can see from the shop floor, the kitchen is already built for you.

Let us now build a new counter area for your coffee shop. Go ahead and open the _Interior Panel_ and choose the _Rooms and Textures_ icon.  Now select the _Counter Area_ under the _Add Rooms_ panel and drag the area of the new room on the floor where you wish to place it.

A word of advice: it is a good idea to always place the counter area as close to the kitchen as possible because your chef will frequently go back and forth between the kitchen and the counter area to use their respective facilities.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]Now that the room is ready, let's start adding some facilities to it. With the _Counter Area_ selected, go to the Interior Panel and click the _Counter Appliances and Facilities_ button and then add a _Front Counter_ to your empty counter area. The _Front Counter_ can serve two functions: a preparation table for the chefs, and also a waiting station for servers to pick up food for delivery.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]A number of cooking equipment can also be placed on top of a _Front Counter_ similar to the _Kitchen Table_ in your restaurants' kitchens. And just like the _Front Counter_, you may also add a _Back Counter_ to your coffee shop if you feel that you don't have enough space to place all your equipment. Now go ahead and try putting all of the missing cooking facilities shown in the _Recipe Menu_ into your counter area.

Once you're finished, simply press the _Next_ button to proceed.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]Excellent! Your coffee shop is now almost ready. Just remember to setup all the remaining furniture, hire adequate staff and prepare the food menu well and you should be on your way to your first coffee shop's grand opening. Good Luck!
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]
